{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782538943,"nonce":"hFbPjpd9fRmtP3VnFY7MTYec8zA=","title":"Query builder: WITH RECURSIVE (recursive CTEs)","message":"Recursive CTEs — `WITH RECURSIVE name AS (\u003canchor\u003e UNION [ALL] \u003crecursive\u003e) …` — for the query builder.\n\nSplit out of d5d1a21 (non-recursive CTEs), which is now complete (PRs #55 flat, #56 nested). Recursion needs a CTE to reference itself plus a UNION between an anchor and a recursive term, so it is blocked on set-operation support (UNION/INTERSECT/EXCEPT).\n\nDepends on: e786bc1 (Subqueries, CTEs, and set operations) — specifically the set-ops piece.\n\nNon-recursive foundation already in place: `#[derive(CTE)]`, `CteDefinition`/`CteDef`, `QuerySource::cte_def`, `Selected::collect_ctes` (transitive closure + topo-order + cycle rejection — the cycle guard is exactly where a self-reference would be allowed once recursion is supported).","files":null}]}